---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import NavOverlay from '../components/NavOverlay.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — PB&J Agency</title>
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,300;1,400;1,600&family=Montserrat:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />

  <style is:global lang="scss">
    @import '../styles/global.scss';
  </style>
</head>

<body class="subpage">
  <Header />
  <NavOverlay />

  <main class="privacy-page">
    <div class="privacy-page__inner wrap">

      <div class="privacy-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="privacy-effective">Effective as of January 1, 2025</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-layout">
      <aside class="privacy-nav">
        <p class="privacy-nav__label">Contents</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#collection">Collection of Your Personal Information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#auto">Automatically Collected Information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#sharing">Sharing Information with Third Parties</a></li>
          <li><a href="#deletion">Right to Deletion</a></li>
          <li><a href="#links">Links</a></li>
          <li><a href="#children">Children Under 13</a></li>
          <li><a href="#storage">External Data Storage</a></li>
          <li><a href="#changes">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <div class="privacy-body">

        <p>PB&amp;J Agency, LLC ("PBJ Agency") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it through compliance with this policy. This policy describes the types of information we may collect from you or that you may provide when you visit this website and our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting, and disclosing that information. PBJ Agency is the data controller for information processed through this website. By using the PBJ Agency website, you consent to the data practices described in this statement.</p>

        <h2 id="collection">Collection of Your Personal Information</h2>
        <p>We do not collect any personal information about you unless you voluntarily provide it to us. However, you may be required to provide certain personal information to us when you elect to utilize certain services. These may include: (a) submitting the Surgeon Application Form or the Partner Inquiry Form; or (b) sending us an email message. We will use your information for, but not limited to, communicating with you in relation to services you have requested from us. We also may gather additional personal or non-personal information in the future.</p>

        <h2 id="auto">Automatically Collected Information</h2>
        <p>Information about your computer hardware and software may be automatically collected by PBJ Agency. This information can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times, and referring website addresses. This information is used for the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the PBJ Agency website.</p>

        <h2 id="sharing">Sharing Information with Third Parties</h2>
        <p>PBJ Agency does not sell, rent, or lease its customer lists to third parties.</p>
        <p>PBJ Agency may share data with trusted partners to help perform statistical analysis, send you email or postal mail, provide customer support, or arrange for deliveries. All such third parties are prohibited from using your personal information except to provide these services to PBJ Agency, and they are required to maintain the confidentiality of your information.</p>
        <p>PBJ Agency may disclose your personal information, without notice, if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to: (a) conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on PBJ Agency or the site; (b) protect and defend the rights or property of PBJ Agency; and/or (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect the personal safety of users of PBJ Agency, or the public.</p>

        <h2 id="deletion">Right to Deletion</h2>
        <p>Subject to certain exceptions set out below, on receipt of a verifiable request from you, we will delete your personal information from our records and direct any service providers to delete your personal information from their records.</p>
        <p>Please note that we may not be able to comply with requests to delete your personal information if it is necessary to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete the transaction for which the personal information was collected, fulfill the terms of a written warranty or product recall conducted in accordance with federal law, provide a good or service requested by you, or reasonably anticipated within the context of our ongoing business relationship with you, or otherwise perform a contract between you and us;</li>
          <li>Detect security incidents, protect against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent, or illegal activity; or prosecute those responsible for that activity;</li>
          <li>Debug to identify and repair errors that impair existing intended functionality;</li>
          <li>Exercise free speech, ensure the right of another consumer to exercise his or her right of free speech, or exercise another right provided for by law;</li>
          <li>Comply with the California Electronic Communications Privacy Act;</li>
          <li>Engage in public or peer-reviewed scientific, historical, or statistical research in the public interest that adheres to all other applicable ethics and privacy laws, when our deletion of the information is likely to render impossible or seriously impair the achievement of such research, provided we have obtained your informed consent;</li>
          <li>Enable solely internal uses that are reasonably aligned with your expectations based on your relationship with us;</li>
          <li>Comply with an existing legal obligation; or</li>
          <li>Otherwise use your personal information, internally, in a lawful manner that is compatible with the context in which you provided the information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="links">Links</h2>
        <p>This website contains links to other sites. Please be aware that we are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of such other sites. We encourage our users to be aware when they leave our site and to read the privacy statements of any other site that collects personally identifiable information.</p>

        <h2 id="children">Children Under 13</h2>
        <p>PBJ Agency does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under the age of thirteen. If you are under the age of thirteen, you must ask your parent or guardian for permission to use this website.</p>

        <h2 id="storage">External Data Storage</h2>
        <p>If you choose to submit your information via the Surgeon Application Form or the Partner Inquiry Form, we may store your data on servers provided by third-party hosting vendors with whom we have contracted.</p>

        <h2 id="changes">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>PBJ Agency reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you about significant changes in the way we treat personal information by placing a prominent notice on our website and/or by updating any privacy information. Your continued use of the website and/or services available after such modifications will constitute your: (a) acknowledgment of the modified Privacy Policy; and (b) agreement to abide and be bound by that Policy.</p>

        <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
        <p>PBJ Agency welcomes your questions or comments regarding this Privacy Policy. If you believe that PBJ Agency has not adhered to this statement, please contact us at:</p>
        <address>
          PB&amp;J Agency, LLC<br />
          Denver, CO<br />
          <a href="mailto:admin@madewithpbj.com">admin@madewithpbj.com</a>
        </address>

      </div>
      </div> <!-- end privacy-layout -->
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <script>
    import '../scripts/main.js';
  </script>
</body>
</html>

<style lang="scss">
  body.subpage {
    background: var(--cream);
  }

  .privacy-page {
    padding-top: 160px;
    padding-bottom: 160px;

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      padding-top: 120px;
      padding-bottom: 100px;
    }
  }

  .privacy-page__inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .privacy-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 48px;
    }
  }

  .privacy-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;

    &__label {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: var(--text-xs);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 3px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    ul {
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0;
    }

    li a {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 12px;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-decoration: none;
      display: block;
      padding: 8px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      line-height: 1.4;
      transition: color 200ms ease;

      &:hover { color: var(--ink); }
    }

    li:first-child a { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  .privacy-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 48px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .privacy-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .privacy-effective {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .privacy-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 32px;

    h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: var(--text-xs);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 3px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    p, address {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: var(--text-base);
      color: var(--ink-mid);
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    address {
      font-style: normal;

      a {
        color: var(--burgundy);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding-bottom: 1px;
        transition: border-color 200ms ease;

        &:hover { border-color: var(--burgundy); }
      }
    }

    ul {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 12px;
      padding-left: 24px;

      li {
        font-family: var(--font-sans);
        font-size: var(--text-base);
        color: var(--ink-mid);
        line-height: 1.8;
      }
    }
  }
</style>
